The former soccer star won the presidential run-off election, succeeding Ellen Johnson Sirleaf - Africa's first elected woman President. Weah, who was sworn in as Liberia's president in January 2018, is under growing pressure over his management of a financial crisis in his impoverished country. However, the Liberian ministry of justice refused to authorise the rally last month, labelling calls for Weah to step down unconstitutional. --African News-- 